<p><a name="Trivia" id="Trivia"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Simon_Critchley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Trivia">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Trivia</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.askmelissa.com/index.php/out-on-the-scene/a-spirited-gathering/" class="external text" title="http://www.askmelissa.com/index.php/out-on-the-scene/a-spirited-gathering/" rel="nofollow">Askmelissa.com</a> How do you applaud the launch of Simon Critchley’s <i>Book of Dead Philosophers?</i> With a séance, of course! At least that’s how the <i>Accompanied Literary Society</i> chose to celebrate at an out-of-this-world party at Bobo.</li>
<li>Under the name of <a href="http://cdbaby.com/cd/critchleysimmons" class="external text" title="http://cdbaby.com/cd/critchleysimmons" rel="nofollow">Critchley &amp; Simmons</a>, Critchley has produced a CD called <i>Humiliation</i> (2004) and a series of short films. This project was launched in an event at the Sydney Opera House in August 2004.</li>
<li>Critchley gave the name <a href="/wiki/The_Bleach_Boys" title="The Bleach Boys">The Bleach Boys</a> to a <a href="/wiki/Hitchin" title="Hitchin">Hitchin</a> based band previously known as <i>The Fur Coughs</i>.</li>
<li>Critchley himself played guitar in a number of North Hertfordshire bands including <i>The Good Blokes</i> and <i>Social Class 5</i>.</li>
</ul>
